# Semantic-Aware Merge Pipeline Implementation Plan

This plan details the design and changes required to refactor the merge engine into a semantic-aware merge pipeline with field-specific reliability and data freshness scoring.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Semantic Matcher Design:** To resolve "dont use LLM instead use embeddings", we will build a hybrid semantic matcher:
> 1. It will first attempt to load a lightweight local sentence-transformers model (e.g., `all-MiniLM-L6-v2`) to compute dense embeddings.
> 2. If `sentence_transformers` is not installed or loading fails (due to CPU/memory constraints), it will automatically fall back to a **pure-Python Char N-Gram TF-IDF Cosine Similarity Embedding** paired with **Jaro-Winkler/Levenshtein distance**.
> 3. This guarantees no LLM calls are used for semantic comparison, keeping execution extremely fast, offline-friendly, and accurate for variations like "Google LLC" vs "Google" and "SWE" vs "Software Engineer".
> **Field-Specific Reliability Matrix:** We will introduce a matrix where different sources have different trust weights per field (e.g., GitHub is highly trusted for `skills`, Resume for `experience`, and CSV for contact details).

